header.gameNote: BASKETBALL TRAVELERS CLASSIC AT SEATTLE WA

article.headline: Northern Iowa 68, Nicholls State 63
article.story: SEATTLE (AP) -- Eric Coleman had 16 points and 15 rebounds to lead Northern Iowa to a 68-63 win over Nicholls State in the opening game of the Basketball Travelers Classic at Bank of America Arena. Coleman was 6-of-11 from the field. Grant Stout had 11 points and 10 rebounds for Northern Iowa (1-0), which won in the coaching debut of Ben Jacobson. Adonis Gray had 20 points on 8-of-14 shooting and nine rebounds for Nicholls State, which rallied from an 11-point deficit to close to within two points at 65-63 with 14.2 seconds left after a Justin Payne 3-pointer. But two Adam Viet free throws preceded a Colonels turnover, and Stout finished off with a free throw. The Colonels (0-2), who opened the season Saturday with a 90-55 loss at Mississippi State and will play four games in four days, are playing without Stefan Blaszczynski. The team's top scorer and rebounder from a year ago, Blaszczynski suffered an ankle injury before the season. After leading 12-5, the Panthers went without a field goal for 7:22 as Nicholls State took its first lead at 17-14. But Northern Iowa responded with five 3-pointers -- including three from Jared Josten -- in the next 4½ minutes to take the lead again at 29-23 and never trailed again.
